#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:372
msgid "Editing Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:373
msgid ""
"Palette styles can be modified with the style editor. There are five "
"types of styles to choose from: plain color, texture, custom, special and"
" vector brush. Custom, special and vector brush styles are available for "
"vector animation levels only. For special and custom styles you also have"
" control over various settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:375
msgid ""
"An option lets you decide whether the editing has to be automatically "
"assigned to the style, or only when you click the Apply button. In the "
"bottom right corner you can see swatches of the old and the new style; if"
" you want to go back to the old style, simply click it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:377
msgid ""
"Only the first style in the palette, labelled No Style, cannot be edited:"
" it allows you to remove any style from lines and filled areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:379
msgid "**To open the style editor as a floating window:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:383
