"editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:404
msgid "Plain Colors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:405
msgid ""
"Plain colors can be defined either by Red, Green and Blue or Hue, "
"Saturation and Value values. They can be used for both drawing lines and "
"filling areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:407
msgid ""
"You can also set the color opacity with the Alpha slider: the lower the "
"value, the more transparent the color. You can check the opacity of the "
"color with the checkerboard pattern visible beneath the color, whose "
"visibility is proportional to the color transparency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:409
msgid ""
"To edit a plain color you can use either the sliders or the color "
"spectrum with its related vertical slider. To pick a color from the "
"sliders or from the spectrum, click it; to adjust values you can use the "
"arrowhead buttons available at each slider ends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:411
msgid "|Toonz71_145|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:413
msgid ""
"By checking a color value next to its label, you can change the way "
"colors are represented in the color spectrum and in the vertical slider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:415
msgid ""
"Plain colors can also be picked from the viewer content by using the RGB "
"Picker tool ( |Toonz71_146| ), whose Type option lets you choose the "
"following: Normal, to pick values of a color; Rectangular, to pick the "
"average values of the colors included in the box you define; Freehand, to"
" pick the average values of the colors included in the area you outline "
"by clicking and dragging; and Polyline, to pick the average values of the"
" colors included in the area you outline by defining a series of lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:419
msgid ""
"If the current style is a special one, the color you edit is the color "
"used by the special style. If the special style uses more than one color,"
" you can select the color to edit in the row of thumbnails available "
"below the color spectrum. (see  :ref:`Special Styles <special_styles>`  "
")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:421
msgid "**To pick the plain color from the viewer content:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:423
msgid "Select the RGB Picker tool ()."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:427
msgid "Click in the viewer to pick the needed color values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:429
msgid ""
"Set the type to Rectangular, then click and drag in the viewer to define "
"a box which picks the average values of the colors included in the box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:431
msgid ""
"Set the type to Freehand, then click and drag in the viewer to outline an"
" area which picks the average values of the colors included in the area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:433
msgid ""
"Set the type to Polyline, then click in the viewer to outline an area by "
"defining a series of lines and this will pick the average values of the "
"colors included in the area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:438
msgid "Textures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:439
msgid ""
"Textures can be used both for drawing lines and filling areas. They can "
"be selected from a list available in the Texture page, where your own "
"textures can be added as well, or added as Custom Texture clicking the "
"Custom Texture button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:441
msgid ""
"Vector texture mapping, that is the way the texture is applied to "
"vectors, is performed using vector parametric coordinates: this means "
"that the texture “follows” the vector’s shape and thickness."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:443
msgid "|Toonz71_148|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:445
msgid ""
"Custom Textures can be loaded both on PLI than TLV levels, but their "
"parameters can be used only on TLV levels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:447
msgid ""
"Lines texture mapping, that is the way the texture is applied to raster "
"drawing lines, and area texture mapping use the standard mapping: the "
"texture image is tiled to cover the lines and the areas painted with the "
"style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:449
msgid ""
"A more powerful texture mapping can be performed by using the Texture and"
" Pinned Texture special FX (see  :ref:`Toonz Level <toonz_level>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:451
msgid "**To add a new Texture:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:453
msgid ""
"Create the image you want to use as a texture with the following "
"characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:455
msgid ""
"The number of pixels of the width and height of the image has to be equal"
" to 2 to the power of any number (i.e. 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, "
"etc.); if not, texture images will be stretched."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:457
msgid ""
"The file has to be saved in any of the following formats: BMP, JPG, NOL, "
"PNG, RGB, SGI, TGA and TIF."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:459
msgid ""
"Save the texture file in the folder ``Projectroot\\library\\textures``  "
"(see  :ref:`Setting up Projects <setting_up_projects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:464
msgid "Custom Textures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:465
msgid ""
"Custom Textures can be used both for drawing lines and filling areas. "
"Using Custom Textures allows to set many parameters such as: use the "
"texture as pattern, using the brightness of the loaded image to modulate "
"the brightness of the color index to which it is applied; choose the "
"position between Fixed (the texture will be fixed and slide into the "
"character), Automatic (the texture will follows the character position "
"during the animation) and Random (the texture position change at each "
"frame in a random way); scale, rotate, apply an Horizontal or Vertical "
"offset and change the Contrast. The Custom Texture will be saved into the"
" Palette and its icon will be replaced with an icon of the loaded "
"texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:467
msgid "**To add a Custom Texture:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:469
msgid "Select a chip color in the palette."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:471
msgid ""
"Go in the Texture page of the Style Editor and press the Custom Texture "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:473
msgid ""
"Using the Load From File field and choose the image (or the image "
"sequence) you want to use as texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:475
msgid "Press the Preview button to visualize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:479
msgid "the texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:484
msgid "Custom Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:485
msgid ""
"Custom styles are available for vector animation levels only. A custom "
"style repeats an image or an animation level, created with Toonz or third"
" party software, along the vectors of a vector animation level. Custom "
"styles cannot be used to paint areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:487
msgid ""
"In the Custom page you can select the image or the animation level you "
"want to use as a style. You can add to the list your own animation levels"
" as well: both Toonz animation levels (PLI) and full-color images or "
"sequences of full-color images (BMP, JPG, NOL, PIC, PICT, PCT, PNG, RGB, "
"SGI, TGA, TIF and TIFF) are supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:489
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:535
msgid ""
"PLI levels are rendered according to the vector length and thickness, "
"thus appearing jagged when zoomed in. If the output format is Flash SWF, "
"then the PLI level will remain vector-based. (see  :ref:`Choosing the "
"Output Settings <choosing_the_output_settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:491
msgid ""
"The images are repeated changing their placement and size according to "
"the vector’s shape and thickness. If the animation levels contains "
"different drawings, they are repeated cyclically along the vector length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:493
msgid ""
"Parameters such as the distance between subsequent images along the "
"vector and their rotation can be defined in the Settings page (see  "
":ref:`Settings <settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:495
msgid "|Toonz71_149|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:497
msgid "**To add a new custom style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:499
msgid ""
"Create an image or an animation level with Toonz, or with third-party "
"software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:501
msgid ""
"Save it in the folder ``Projectroot\\library\\custom styles`` (see  "
":ref:`Setting up Projects <setting_up_projects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:506
msgid "Special Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:507
msgid ""
"Special styles use a number of mathematical functions to create effects "
"that can be used either for vectors or for filling areas defined by "
"vectors. They can be selected from a list available in the Special page, "
"where styles suitable for vectors have a thumbnail representing how they "
"will look as a line; styles suitable for filling have a thumbnail "
"representing a corner piece of an area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:509
msgid ""
"Special styles can simulate for instance a frieze, a leaf, or a pencil "
"stroke along a vector, or allow you to fill areas with special effects "
"such as polka dots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:511
msgid ""
"Special styles can be customized by defining the parameters available in "
"the Settings page. This allows you to have many similar styles, each with"
" a different configuration of settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:513
msgid "|Toonz71_150|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:515
msgid ""
"Colors used by specials can be modified by using the Plain page available"
" in the style editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:517
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:543
msgid ""
"The first item available in the list allows you to remove the special in "
"order to return to the plain color style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:519
msgid "**To change colors used by a special style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:521
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:553
msgid "Move to the Plain page in the Style Editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:523
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:555
msgid "Edit the color using the spectrum and sliders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:525
msgid ""
"If the special uses more than one color, select the color to edit in the "
"row of swatches available below the color spectrum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:530
msgid "Vector Brush"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:531
msgid ""
"Vector brush styles are available for vector animation levels only. A "
"vector brush applies a vector image, created with Toonz, along the "
"vectors of a vector animation level. Vector brush styles cannot be used "
"to paint areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:533
msgid ""
"In the Vector Brush page you can select the image you want to use as a "
"style. You can add to the list your own PLI images as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:537
msgid ""
"The Vector Brush image is applyed to each stroke of the drawing that use "
"this style according to the stroke’s shape and thickness. If the "
"animation levels used as vector Brush contains different drawings, only "
"the first is taken into account"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:539
msgid "|Toonz71_151|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:541
msgid ""
"Colors used by vector brushes can be modified by using the Plain page "
"available in the style editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:545
msgid "**To add a new vector brush:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:547
msgid "Create a PLI level with Toonz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:549
msgid ""
"Save it in the folder ``Projectroot\\library\\vector brushes`` (see  "
":ref:`Setting up Projects <setting_up_projects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:551
msgid "**To change colors used by a vector brush style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:557
msgid ""
"If the vector brush uses more than one color, select the color to edit in"
" the row of swatches available below the color spectrum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:562
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:563
msgid "The Settings page is available for defining some color properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:565
msgid ""
"For Smart Raster levels, it contains only the Autopaint for Lines option,"
" that can be used to paint automatically lines with the fill color when "
"painting the level (see  :ref:`Using the Autopaint for Lines Option "
"<using_the_autopaint_for_lines_option>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:567
msgid ""
"For Vector levels, it contains parameters only when the style is a "
"custom or a special one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:569
msgid ""
"When the style is a custom, the Settings page contains two sliders: the "
"Distance sets the space between two subsequent images of the animation "
"level used as custom; the Rotation sets the angle of all the images. When"
" the style is a special, the Settings page contains one or more sliders "
"that allow you to calibrate the predefined style for your needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:571
msgid "|Toonz71_152|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:573
msgid ""
"You can add the same custom or special style as many times as you want, "
"each time defining different settings for it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:578
msgid "Changing the Type of Style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:579
msgid ""
"When you select a plain color, a texture, a custom, a special or a vector"
" brush style in the style editor, you automatically assign it to the "
"current style, thus changing the type of style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:581
msgid ""
"The only exception is when you want to change from a special or a vector "
"brush style to a plain color, because when the current style is a special"
" or a vector brush one, the Plain page is for setting its colors. In this"
" case you have first to remove the special or vector brush style by using"
" the first swatch available in the swatch list, and then move to the "
"Plain page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:583
msgid ""
"Note that when you change from a style suitable for both lines and areas "
"to a style suitable only for lines, areas painted with that style will "
"become invisible, and vice versa. For example if you change a style from "
"plain color to custom, all areas painted with that plain color will "
"become invisible. If you modify the style so that it is suitable again "
"for lines and areas, the invisible parts will become visible again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:585
msgid "**To change the type of style from plain color to any other:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:587
msgid "Choose an item in the texture, special or Custom page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:589
msgid "**To change the type of style to plain color:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:591
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:597
msgid ""
"Choose the Plain page and start moving a slider or the selector in the "
"color spectrum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:593
msgid ""
"**To change the type of style from special or vector brush to plain "
"color:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:595
msgid ""
"In the Special or vector brush page select the first style in the list, "
"the top-left most style, to assign no special style to the current color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:602
msgid "Editing Several Styles at the Same Time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:603
msgid ""
"You can modify several styles at the same time by using the Palette "
"Gizmo. It allows you to change the luminance, saturation and transparency"
" of the selected styles, blend them, or fade them to a specific color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:605
msgid ""
"Only the plain colors are affected by the Palette Gizmo editing and the "
"blending. e , special styles and custom styles will not be affected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:607
msgid "**To open the Palette Gizmo:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:614
msgid ""
"Click the Palette Gizmo button ( |Toonz71_154| ) available in the bottom "
"bar of the palette."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:616
msgid ""
"Right-click the selected styles and choose Palette Gizmo from the menu "
"that opens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:618
msgid "**To change the luminance of the selected styles:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:620
msgid "Set the percentage of variation you want to apply to the styles luminance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:624
msgid "Click the + button to increase the luminance of the set percentage."
